[22:00:40    18] codex
[22:00:40    18] The C header and bundled tests confirm this is not an opaque Rust-only type: callers construct and traverse `cJSON`’s `next`/`prev`/`child` links and string pointers directly. I’m recording that compatibility constraint and validating the untouched baseline rather than substituting `Box`/`Vec` in a way that would silently change the C ABI or allocator behavior.
