[22:20:45    81] +## Current target / next steps
[22:20:45    81]  
[22:20:45    81] -- `cJSON_New_Item` now returns `Option<NonNull<cJSON>>` instead of a raw
[22:20:45    81] -  pointer. Its existing callers convert that safe internal result back to a
[22:20:45    81] -  null raw pointer only at their C-facing linked-list/allocation boundaries.
[22:20:45    81] -  This removes a raw pointer from an implementation function signature while
[22:20:45    81] -  retaining hook allocation and failure behavior.
[22:20:45    81] -- Removed the obsolete `raw_ref_op` feature gate; raw-reference syntax is
