[22:20:45    81] +   the printer migration fully behavior-equivalent.
[22:20:45    81] +3. Then isolate raw C-tree/string reads at the exported printer boundaries.
[22:20:45    81] +   `cJSON` is explicitly non-opaque: C tests initialize/walk `child`, `next`,
[22:20:45    81] +   `prev`, `string`, and `valuestring`, so those fields cannot simply become
[22:20:45    81] +   `Box`/`Vec` without an ABI/compatibility decision.
