[22:20:45    81] -## Blocker reconfirmed: printer string boundary (2026-07-17)
[22:20:45    81] +## Constraints / pitfalls
[22:20:45    81]  
[22:20:45    81] -- Re-audited the smallest remaining printer unit, `print_string_ptr`, and its
[22:20:45    82] -  `printbuffer` callers. A safe printer would need both a safe owned output
[22:20:45    82] -  buffer and a safe tree/string view. `printbuffer` is backed by the active C
[22:20:45    82] -  allocator hook (or an FFI caller's preallocated byte buffer), while the
[22:20:45    82] -  input comes from public `cJSON` raw string and linked-node fields. Neither
[22:20:45    82] -  view can be formed in implementation code without raw conversion.
[22:20:45    82] -- Confirmed the compatibility constraint rather than relying only on the
[22:20:45    82] -  header: bundled C tests directly initialize and walk `child`, `next`, and
[22:20:45    82] -  `prev`, and inspect `string`/`valuestring` (`tests/parse_object.c` and
[22:20:45    82] -  `tests/misc_tests.c`). `cJSON` is therefore expressly non-opaque despite
[22:20:45    82] -  being passed through pointers in the exported ABI. Replacing those fields
[22:20:45    82] -  with `Box`/`Vec`/`Rc` would break supported C use and custom-hook ownership.
[22:20:45    82] -- The checker attributes all remaining implementation-level unsafe work to
[22:20:45    82] -  eight helpers (currently 60 total findings including FFI):
[22:20:45    82] -  `parse_string`, `print_string_ptr`, `parse_value`, `print_value`,
[22:20:45    82] -  `parse_array`, `print_array`, `parse_object`, and `print_object`.
[22:20:45    82] -  These helpers are one compatibility cluster: `parse_string` must write into
[22:20:45    82] -  hook-allocated storage; the parsers construct the C-visible linked nodes;
[22:20:45    82] -  the printers read those nodes and C strings and write into hook/caller-owned
[22:20:45    82] -  output storage. They cannot be split into safe pieces without changing the
[22:20:45    82] -  public representation or allocator contract.
[22:20:45    82] -- Re-ran `check-unsafe2` and filtered out exported entry points. There are no
[22:20:45    82] -  additional candidates: exactly those eight helpers remain, with 60 findings
[22:20:45    82] -  total across the crate. Their implementation-only findings are respectively
[22:20:45    82] -  `parse_string` (1), `print_string_ptr` (3), `parse_value` (2),
[22:20:45    82] -  `print_value` (5), `parse_array` (6), `print_array` (12), `parse_object`
